{
"explanation": "A file system is a way of organizing and storing files on a computer or digital device. It is a method for keeping track of files and directories, and it provides an interface that allows users and applications to access and manipulate files. File systems can be implemented in a variety of ways, including on hard drives, solid-state drives, and network-attached storage systems. They can also be used with different types of operating systems, such as Windows, macOS, and Linux. Some common file system formats include NTFS, HFS+, and ext4." }
